00:52.195 --> 00:54.949
<i>The second star to the right</i>

00:55.032 --> 00:58.828
<i>Shines in the night for you</i>

00:58.911 --> 01:02.291
<i>To tell you that the dreams you plan</i>

01:02.374 --> 01:06.629
<i>Really can come true</i>

01:06.713 --> 01:09.507
<i>The second star to the right</i>

01:09.591 --> 01:14.054
<i>Shines with a light so rare</i>

01:14.138 --> 01:18.059
<i>And if it's Never Land you need</i>

01:18.143 --> 01:22.189
<i>Its light will lead you there</i>

01:22.273 --> 01:25.152
<i>Twinkle, twinkle little star</i>

01:25.235 --> 01:29.406
<i>So we'll know where you are</i>

01:29.489 --> 01:33.494
<i>Gleaming in the skies above</i>

01:33.578 --> 01:36.291
<i>Lead us to the land</i>

01:36.374 --> 01:40.838
<i>We dream of</i>

01:40.921 --> 01:45.135
<i>And when our journey is through</i>

01:45.218 --> 01:47.846
<i>Each time we say</i>

01:47.930 --> 01:50.892
<i>Good night</i>

01:50.975 --> 01:56.732
<i>We'll thank the little star
that shines</i>

01:57.816 --> 02:02.113
<i>The second from</i>

02:02.197 --> 02:05.660
<i>The right</i>

02:09.914 --> 02:12.376
All this has happened before.

02:12.459 --> 02:15.588
And it will all happen again.

02:15.672 --> 02:18.675
But this time
it happened in London.

02:21.428 --> 02:25.809
It happened on a quiet street
in Bloomsbury.

02:25.892 --> 02:30.731
That corner house over there is
the home of the Darling family.

02:30.815 --> 02:33.317
And Peter Pan chose
this particular house...

02:33.401 --> 02:37.072
because there were people
here who believed in him.

02:37.155 --> 02:40.535
There was Mrs Darling.

02:40.618 --> 02:44.622
George, dear, do hurry. We mustn't
be late for the party, you know.

02:44.706 --> 02:49.211
Mrs Darling believed that Peter Pan
was the spirit of youth.

02:49.295 --> 02:53.258
- But Mr Darling...
- Mary, unless I find my cuff links...

02:53.341 --> 02:55.469
we don't go to the party.

02:55.553 --> 02:59.724
And if we don't go to the party, I can
never show my face in the office again.

02:59.807 --> 03:01.727
And if I can never... Ouch!

03:01.810 --> 03:05.691
Well, Mr Darling
was a practical man.

03:05.774 --> 03:09.028
The boys, however,
John and Michael...

03:09.111 --> 03:11.531
believed Peter Pan
was a real person...

03:11.615 --> 03:15.244
and made him the hero
of all their nursery games.

03:15.328 --> 03:17.371
Blast you, Peter Pan!

03:19.457 --> 03:23.128
Take that! Give up,
Captain Hook? Give up?

03:23.211 --> 03:26.341
Never! I'll teach you
to cut off me hand!

03:26.424 --> 03:29.761
Oh, no, John.
It was the left hand.

03:29.844 --> 03:31.972
Oh, yes.
Thank you, Wendy.

03:32.056 --> 03:36.102
Wendy, the eldest,
not only believed...

03:36.186 --> 03:38.772
she was the supreme authority
on Peter Pan...

03:38.855 --> 03:40.775
and all his
marvellous adventures.

03:40.858 --> 03:44.612
Oh, Nana, must we always
take that nasty tonic?

03:44.695 --> 03:48.033
Nana, the nursemaid,
being a dog...

03:48.116 --> 03:50.620
kept her opinions to herself...

03:50.703 --> 03:54.207
and viewed the whole affair
with a certain tolerance.

04:01.299 --> 04:02.801
Take that!

04:02.968 --> 04:06.180
Insolent boy!
I'll slash you to ribbons!

04:06.305 --> 04:09.100
And I'll cut you to pieces.

04:09.183 --> 04:11.687
- Aha!
- Ouch!

04:11.770 --> 04:15.858
- Careful, Michael, my glasses.
- I'm sorry, John.

04:15.942 --> 04:18.444
You'll never leave
this ship alive!

04:18.528 --> 04:22.031
Oh, yes, I will.
Take that!

04:27.956 --> 04:31.878
Scuttle me bones, boy,
I'll slit your gizzard.

04:31.962 --> 04:33.797
Oh, no, you won't.

04:33.880 --> 04:37.176
Back, back, back, you villain!

04:37.260 --> 04:40.514
- Insolent pup!
- Wicked pirate!

04:40.597 --> 04:45.395
- Aha, I got ya.
- You didn't either. You never touched me.

04:45.478 --> 04:49.232
Take that and that!
And that!

04:49.316 --> 04:51.527
Boys, boys,
less noise, please.

04:54.447 --> 04:57.534
- Oh, hello, Father.
- You old bilge rat.

04:57.617 --> 05:00.120
Wh-Wh-What?
Now, see here, Michael...

05:00.203 --> 05:03.958
Oh, not you, Father.
You see, he's Peter Pan.

05:04.042 --> 05:07.046
- And John's Captain Hook.
- Yes, yes, of course.

05:07.129 --> 05:09.798
Uh, have you seen my cuff...

05:09.882 --> 05:12.802
Oh, Nana,
for goodness sake!

05:12.886 --> 05:15.556
Where are those cuff links?

05:15.640 --> 05:19.977
- Cuff links, Father?
- Yes, the gold ones.

05:20.061 --> 05:23.231
Michael, the buried treasure.
Where is it?

05:23.315 --> 05:25.443
- I don't know.
- The map then.

05:25.526 --> 05:28.571
- Where's the treasure map?
- It got lost.

05:28.655 --> 05:31.867
- Good heavens, my shirt front!
- Hurray! You found it!

05:31.950 --> 05:34.536
- You found it!
- Yes, so I have.

05:34.620 --> 05:37.916
And hereafter...
Don't paw me, Michael.

05:37.999 --> 05:43.255
This is my last clean...
No! No!

05:43.339 --> 05:46.093
George, dear, we really must
hurry or we'll be late...

05:46.176 --> 05:49.930
- Mary, look!
- George.

05:50.013 --> 05:53.267
- It's only chalk, Father.
- Why, Michael.

05:53.351 --> 05:56.271
It's not his fault.
It's in the story.

05:56.355 --> 05:59.484
- And Wendy says...
- Wendy? Story?

05:59.567 --> 06:04.323
I might have known. Wendy!

06:04.407 --> 06:07.202
- Wendy!
- Yes, Father?

06:07.285 --> 06:10.372
- Would you kindly ex...
- Oh, Mother!

06:10.456 --> 06:13.626
- You look simply lovely.
- Thank you, dear.

06:13.710 --> 06:15.963
- Wendy.
- Just my old gown made over.

06:16.046 --> 06:19.466
- But it did turn out rather nicely, didn't...
- Mary, if you don't mind.

06:19.550 --> 06:23.388
- I'd like...
- Why, Father, what have you done to your shirt?

06:23.471 --> 06:27.393
What have I... Oh!

06:27.476 --> 06:32.357
- Now, George, really. It comes right off.
- That's no excuse.

06:32.441 --> 06:37.488
Wendy, haven't I warned you? Stuffing the
boys' heads with a lot of silly stories.

06:37.572 --> 06:40.408
- Oh, but they aren't.
- I say they are.

06:40.491 --> 06:42.995
Captain Crook!
Peter Pirate!

06:43.078 --> 06:47.542
- Peter Pan, Father.
- Pan! Pirate! Poppycock!

06:47.625 --> 06:49.669
- Oh, no, Father. Father, have you...
- Oh, you don't understand.

06:49.753 --> 06:54.550
Absolute poppycock!
And let me tell you, this ridiculous...

06:54.633 --> 06:58.221
- Now, George.
- "Now, George".

06:58.305 --> 07:00.432
"Now, George"!

07:00.515 --> 07:03.269
Well, "Now, George,"
will have his say!

07:03.353 --> 07:07.524
- Please, dear.
- Mary, the child's growing up.

07:07.608 --> 07:09.943
It's high time she had
a room of her own.

07:10.027 --> 07:12.364
- Father!
- George!
- What?

07:12.447 --> 07:15.575
- No!
- I mean it!

07:15.659 --> 07:19.372
Young lady, this is your
last night in the nursery.

07:19.455 --> 07:22.542
And that's my last word
on the matter...

07:35.643 --> 07:38.020
No!

07:39.980 --> 07:41.566
No!

07:49.492 --> 07:52.913
Oh!

07:55.082 --> 07:57.377
Poor Nana.

07:57.544 --> 08:00.046
"Poor Nana"?

08:00.130 --> 08:02.425
This is the last straw!

08:02.508 --> 08:04.844
Out! Out, I say!

08:04.927 --> 08:07.848
- No, Father, no!
- Yes!

08:07.931 --> 08:11.019
There'll be no more dogs
for nursemaids in this house!

08:12.437 --> 08:14.188
Goodbye, Nana.

08:16.108 --> 08:20.237
"Poor Nana".
Oh, yes, "Poor Nana".

08:20.320 --> 08:24.284
But "Poor Father"?
Oh, no!

08:24.367 --> 08:26.871
Blast it!
Where is that rope?

08:28.122 --> 08:31.209
Oh, thank you.

08:35.172 --> 08:38.092
Dash it all, Nana,
don't look at me like that.

08:38.176 --> 08:40.553
It's nothing personal.
It's just that...

08:42.056 --> 08:43.974
Well, you're not really
a nurse at all.

08:44.058 --> 08:47.145
You're, well, a dog.

08:47.228 --> 08:50.315
And the children aren't puppies.
They're people.

08:50.398 --> 08:54.488
And sooner or later, Nana,
people have to grow up.

08:54.571 --> 08:57.492
But, Mother,
I don't want to grow up.

08:57.575 --> 09:01.830
Now, dear, don't worry
about it any more tonight.

09:01.914 --> 09:05.834
He called Peter Pan
"absolute poppycock".

09:05.919 --> 09:10.673
I'm sure he didn't mean it, John.
Father was just upset.

09:10.757 --> 09:15.429
Poor Nana,
out there all alone.

09:15.513 --> 09:18.558
No more tears, Michael.
It's a warm night.

09:18.642 --> 09:20.852
She'll be all right.

09:20.937 --> 09:23.690
- Mother.
- What is it, dear?

09:23.773 --> 09:27.611
- Buried treasure.
- Now, children.

09:27.695 --> 09:30.280
Don't judge your father
too harshly.

09:30.364 --> 09:34.703
After all, he really
loves you very much.

09:34.786 --> 09:37.415
Oh, don't lock it, Mother.
He might come back.

09:37.498 --> 09:41.169
- "He"?
- Yes, uh, Peter Pan.

09:41.253 --> 09:45.340
You see, I found something
that belongs to him.

09:45.424 --> 09:49.220
- Oh? And what's that?
- His shadow.

09:49.303 --> 09:52.766
- "Shadow"?
- Mmm, Nana had it.

09:52.850 --> 09:55.894
But I...
I took it away.

09:57.397 --> 10:02.403
Oh? Yes, of course.

10:02.486 --> 10:04.822
Good night, dear.

10:07.159 --> 10:10.912
But, George, do you think the children
will be safe without Nana?

10:10.997 --> 10:13.291
Safe? Of course
they'll be safe. Why not?

10:13.374 --> 10:16.754
Well, Wendy said something
about a shadow, and I...

10:16.837 --> 10:19.631
- Shadow? Whose shadow?
- Peter Pan's.

10:19.715 --> 10:23.304
Oh, Peter Pan...
Peter Pan!

10:23.387 --> 10:28.143
You don't say. Goodness gracious,
whatever shall we do?

10:28.226 --> 10:30.270
- But, George... Really, I...
- Sound the alarm!

10:30.353 --> 10:33.191
- Call Scotland Yard!
- There must have been someone.

10:33.274 --> 10:36.695
Oh, Mary, of all the impossible,
childish fiddle-faddle.

10:37.029 --> 10:41.451
Peter Pan indeed. How can we expect the
children to grow up and be practical...

10:41.534 --> 10:43.995
- George, dear.
- When you're as bad as they are.

10:44.079 --> 10:46.957
- Please.
- No wonder Wendy gets these idiotic ideas.

11:18.245 --> 11:20.580
Over there, Tink,
in its den.

11:20.664 --> 11:23.501
Is it there?

11:25.336 --> 11:27.673
Must be here somewhere.

11:33.304 --> 11:36.015
Tink! Shh!

11:36.099 --> 11:40.187
Stop playing
and help me find my shadow.

11:40.271 --> 11:43.442
Shadow. Oh, shadow.

12:09.974 --> 12:12.728
Huh?

12:30.916 --> 12:32.418
Aha!

12:41.930 --> 12:46.142
Peter Pan! Oh, Peter!

12:46.226 --> 12:49.647
I knew you'd come back.
I saved your shadow for you.

12:49.730 --> 12:51.817
Oh, I do hope it isn't rumpled.

12:51.900 --> 12:54.569
You know, you look exactly
the way I thought you would.

12:54.653 --> 12:57.365
Oh, a little taller perhaps.
But then...

12:57.448 --> 13:00.451
Oh, you can't stick it
on with soap, Peter.

13:00.535 --> 13:03.455
It needs sewing.
That's the proper way to do it.

13:03.539 --> 13:05.958
Although, come to think of it,
I've never thought about it before.

13:06.041 --> 13:08.002
Uh, sewing shadows, I mean. Of course, I

13:08.003 --> 13:10.213
knew it was your shadow
the minute I saw it.

13:10.296 --> 13:13.551
And I said to myself, I said, "I'll
put it away for him until he comes back.

13:13.634 --> 13:17.640
Oh, he's sure to come back".
And you did, didn't you, Peter?

13:17.723 --> 13:19.559
After all, one can't leave his shadow

13:19.560 --> 13:21.854
lying about and not
miss it sooner or later.

13:21.937 --> 13:24.398
Uh, don't you agree?
But what I still don't

13:24.399 --> 13:27.152
understand is how Nana
got it in the first place.

13:27.235 --> 13:30.321
She really isn't... Oh, sit down.
It won't take long.

13:30.405 --> 13:33.409
She really isn't vicious, you know.
She's a wonderful nurse.

13:33.492 --> 13:35.870
- Although Father says...
- Girls talk too much.

13:35.953 --> 13:39.499
Yes, girls talk too...
Hmm? Oh.

13:39.583 --> 13:43.212
- Well, get on with it, girl.
- Uh, my name is Wendy.

13:43.296 --> 13:46.340
- Uh, Wendy Moira Angela Darl...
- Wendy's enough.

13:46.424 --> 13:50.095
Oh, uh, but how did
Nana get your shadow, Peter?

13:50.179 --> 13:52.849
Jumped at me the other night
at the window.

13:52.932 --> 13:54.517
Well, what were
you doing there?

13:54.601 --> 13:58.606
- I came to listen to the stories.
- My stories?

13:58.689 --> 14:01.025
- But they're all about you.
- Of course.

14:01.108 --> 14:04.404
That's why I like 'em.
I tell 'em to the Lost Boys.

14:04.488 --> 14:07.366
The Lost Boys...
Oh, I remember.

14:07.450 --> 14:09.243
- They're your men.
- Uh-huh.

14:09.327 --> 14:13.373
I'm so glad you came back tonight.
I might never have seen you.

14:13.457 --> 14:15.876
- Why?
- Because I have to grow up tomorrow.

14:15.959 --> 14:19.172
- Grow up!
- Tonight's my last night in the nursery.

14:19.255 --> 14:22.218
But that means
no more stories.

14:22.301 --> 14:24.804
- Mm-hmm.
- No!

14:24.887 --> 14:27.057
I won't have it.
Come on!

14:27.140 --> 14:29.226
Bu-Bu-But
where are we going?

14:29.309 --> 14:32.230
To Never Land.

14:32.313 --> 14:35.108
- Never Land!
- You'll never grow up there.

14:35.191 --> 14:39.655
Oh, Peter,
it will be so wonderful.

14:39.738 --> 14:43.326
But wait.
What would Mother say?

14:43.409 --> 14:45.329
Mother? What's Mother?

14:45.412 --> 14:50.460
Why, Peter, a mother is someone who...
who loves and cares for you.

14:50.544 --> 14:53.965
- And... And tells you stories...
- Good! You can be our mother.

14:54.048 --> 14:55.967
- Come on.
- Now, just a minute, I...

14:56.050 --> 14:58.387
Let me see now.
L-I have to pack.

14:58.470 --> 15:01.683
Oh, and I must leave a note when I'll be
back. Of course, I couldn't stay too long.

15:01.766 --> 15:04.936
And then I'll have to...
Oh, but Never Land.

15:05.019 --> 15:07.690
Oh, I...
I-I'm so happy I...

15:07.773 --> 15:11.444
I think I'll give you a... a kiss.

15:14.114 --> 15:16.116
What's a... a kiss?

15:16.199 --> 15:19.704
Oh, well, uh,
I-I'll show you.

15:19.787 --> 15:21.832
- Oh!
- Stop! Stop it, Tink!

15:27.005 --> 15:30.133
John, John, wake up!
He's here.

15:30.216 --> 15:34.013
Huh? Jiminy!

15:34.096 --> 15:36.390
Ooh, what in the world was that?

15:36.474 --> 15:38.810
Tinker Bell.
Don't know what got into her.

15:38.894 --> 15:41.188
Hello, Peter Pan.
I'm Michael.

15:41.271 --> 15:43.983
And my name is John.
How do you do?

15:44.066 --> 15:47.070
- Hello.
- Oh, look, a firefly.

15:47.154 --> 15:49.531
- A pixie.
- Amazing!

15:52.410 --> 15:55.163
- What's the pixie doing?
- Talking.

15:55.246 --> 15:58.250
- What did she say?
- She says you're a big, ugly girl.

16:00.252 --> 16:03.799
Oh. Well, I think
she's lovely.

16:05.467 --> 16:08.638
- Well, come on, Wendy, let's go.
- Where are we going?

16:08.721 --> 16:10.932
- To Never Land.
- Never Land!

16:11.015 --> 16:13.019
- Peter's taking us.
- "Us"?

16:13.102 --> 16:16.523
Well, of course. L-I couldn't
go without Michael and John.

16:16.606 --> 16:20.361
Oh, I should like very much to cross
swords with some real buccaneers.

16:20.444 --> 16:24.533
Yes, and fight pirates too.

16:24.616 --> 16:27.703
Well, all right,
but ya gotta take orders.

16:27.787 --> 16:30.206
- Aye, aye, sir.
- Me too.

16:30.414 --> 16:32.876
But, Peter, how do
we get to Never Land?

16:32.960 --> 16:35.712
- Fly, of course.
- "Fly"?

16:35.796 --> 16:40.385
It's easy. All you
have to do is to... is to...

16:40.468 --> 16:43.472
Is to...

16:43.556 --> 16:46.392
- Ha! That's funny.
- What's the matter?

16:46.475 --> 16:48.562
- Don't you know?
- Oh, sure.

16:48.645 --> 16:52.066
It's... It's just that
I never thought about it before.

16:52.150 --> 16:55.611
Say, that's it!
You think of a wonderful thought.

16:55.695 --> 16:58.449
- Any happy, little thought?
- Uh-huh.

16:58.532 --> 17:01.743
- Like toys at Christmas?
- Sleigh bells, snow?

17:01.827 --> 17:04.455
Yep! Watch me now.
Here I go!

17:05.665 --> 17:08.294
It's easier than pie.

17:08.377 --> 17:11.088
- He can fly!
- He can fly!

17:11.172 --> 17:13.800
He flewed!

17:13.884 --> 17:18.138
- Now you try.
- I'll think of a mermaid lagoon...

17:19.182 --> 17:21.767
underneath a magic moon.

17:21.851 --> 17:24.146
I'll think I'm
in a pirate's cave.

17:24.229 --> 17:26.147
I think I'll be
an Indian brave.

17:26.231 --> 17:28.151
Now everybody try.

17:28.233 --> 17:31.529
One, two, three!

17:31.613 --> 17:35.534
We can fly! We can fly!
We can fly!

17:42.586 --> 17:45.172
This won't do.
What's the matter with you?

17:45.255 --> 17:48.718
All it takes
is faith and trust.

17:48.802 --> 17:52.765
Oh! And something
I forgot. Dust!

17:52.848 --> 17:55.518
- Dust?
- Dust?

17:55.601 --> 18:00.816
Yep, just a little bit
of pixie dust.

18:06.072 --> 18:09.326
Now, think of
the happiest things.

18:09.409 --> 18:12.747
- It's the same as having wings.
- Let's all try it just once more.

18:12.831 --> 18:15.041
Look! We're rising off the floor.

18:15.124 --> 18:18.879
- Jiminy!
- Oh, my! We can fly!

18:18.963 --> 18:23.385
- You can fly!
- We can fly!

18:23.593 --> 18:28.057
Come on, everybody.
Here we go!

18:28.141 --> 18:29.559
Off to Never Land!

18:35.774 --> 18:38.570
<i>Think of a wonderful thought</i>

18:38.653 --> 18:41.364
<i>Any merry little thought</i>

18:41.447 --> 18:43.784
<i>Think of Christmas
Think of snow</i>

18:43.868 --> 18:48.707
<i>Think of sleigh bells
Off you go like reindeer in the sky</i>

18:48.790 --> 18:53.045
<i>You can fly, you can fly
You can fly</i>

18:53.129 --> 18:56.215
<i>Think of the happiest things</i>

18:56.299 --> 18:58.969
<i>It's the same as having wings</i>

18:59.052 --> 19:01.305
<i>Take the path that moonbeams make</i>

19:01.388 --> 19:06.812
<i>If the moon is still awake
you'll see him wink his eye</i>

19:06.896 --> 19:10.734
<i>You can fly, you can fly
You can fly</i>

19:11.985 --> 19:14.071
<i>Up you go with a heigh and ho</i>

19:14.155 --> 19:16.365
<i>To the stars beyond the blue</i>

19:16.449 --> 19:20.078
<i>There's a Never Land
waiting for you</i>

19:20.162 --> 19:24.792
<i>Where all your
happy dreams come true</i>

19:24.876 --> 19:30.424
<i>Every dream that you dream
will come true</i>

19:30.508 --> 19:32.719
Come on, Nana!

19:32.802 --> 19:36.306
<i>When there's a smile
in your heart</i>

19:36.389 --> 19:41.979
<i>There's no better time to start</i>

19:42.063 --> 19:44.316
<i>Think of all the joy you'll find</i>

19:44.399 --> 19:49.405
<i>When you leave the world behind
and bid your cares goodbye</i>

19:49.489 --> 19:52.660
