- Well, at last Captain Hook's comin' to his senses.
- Odd's fish!

41:24.014 --> 41:27.144
I told him all along you Indians
wouldn't betray Peter Pan.

41:27.227 --> 41:31.774
And just what do you think
you are doing, Mr Smee?

41:31.858 --> 41:36.029
Just what you told me, Captain.
Carryin' out your orders.

41:36.113 --> 41:40.785
- My orders?
- Why, yes, Captain. Didn't you just say to go...

41:40.869 --> 41:44.372
Put her back!
You blithering idiot!

41:44.456 --> 41:50.171
- My orders. Of all the bumbling...
- Mr Smee!

41:50.254 --> 41:53.467
Just exactly what do you
think you are doing?

41:53.550 --> 41:56.095
Putting her back
like you said, Captain.

41:56.179 --> 41:58.389
I said nothing of the sort!

41:58.473 --> 42:01.435
Oh, but, C-Captain, d-d-didn't you?
I thought that...

42:01.518 --> 42:03.562
For the last time, Mr Smee.

42:03.645 --> 42:07.817
Take the princess
back to her people.

42:07.901 --> 42:12.990
Understand? Understand?
Understand? Understand?

42:13.073 --> 42:17.037
- Uh, aye, aye, sir.
- Oh, and one more thing.

42:17.120 --> 42:20.248
When you return to the ship,
tell the whole crew...

42:20.332 --> 42:23.044
to help themselves
to me best rum.

42:24.587 --> 42:28.676
- Peter!
- Here's your spirit, Smee!

42:29.677 --> 42:31.847
Why, it's Peter Pan.

42:34.725 --> 42:37.104
- Scurvy brat!
- Thank you, Captain.

42:37.187 --> 42:41.109
Come down, boy,
if you've a taste for cold steel.

42:41.192 --> 42:44.529
- Watch this, Wendy.
- Oh, Peter, do be careful.

42:57.837 --> 43:00.674
- Try your luck, Mr Smee?
- Let him have it!

43:02.217 --> 43:05.680
Well, come on, you idiot!
Blast him!

43:05.763 --> 43:08.307
Right here, Mr Smee.

43:08.391 --> 43:11.562
Hold it, you fool!
No! No!

43:15.065 --> 43:17.819
Captain?

43:17.902 --> 43:19.821
Oh, how dreadful.

43:19.904 --> 43:24.827
What a pity, Mr Smee.
I'm afraid we've lost the dear Captain.

43:27.581 --> 43:29.749
Captain!

43:29.833 --> 43:31.586
In the back, Captain?

43:38.594 --> 43:40.638
Give it to him, Captain!

43:40.722 --> 43:43.516
Cleave him to the brisket.

43:55.323 --> 43:59.036
I've got you this time, Pan.

44:03.249 --> 44:07.379
Well, well, a codfish on a hook.

44:07.463 --> 44:11.843
I'll get you for this, Pan,
if it's the last thing I do!

44:13.762 --> 44:16.808
I say, Captain,
do you hear something?

44:16.891 --> 44:19.143
No.

44:19.769 --> 44:21.146
No!

44:25.985 --> 44:27.987
No!

44:29.781 --> 44:32.993
Mr Crocodile,
do you like codfish?

44:33.077 --> 44:35.496
- You do?
- Oh, Peter, no!

44:43.673 --> 44:45.508
No!

44:47.177 --> 44:49.596
- Smee!
- D-Don't go away, Captain!

44:49.680 --> 44:53.143
Uh, stay right there now, sir.
I'll save ya, sir.

44:56.021 --> 44:58.190
Smee!

44:59.066 --> 45:00.609
Smee!

45:06.033 --> 45:09.537
Smee!

45:12.040 --> 45:13.750
Ow!

45:16.629 --> 45:18.548
Captain! Captain!

45:18.631 --> 45:22.429
Smee! Smee!

45:22.512 --> 45:24.431
- Give him back!
- Smee...

45:27.268 --> 45:31.565
Row for the ship!
Row for the ship...

45:34.151 --> 45:35.904
Whoa!

45:39.449 --> 45:42.745
Smee!

45:44.580 --> 45:47.501
Peter, what about Tiger Lily?

45:47.584 --> 45:50.128
Tiger Lily?
Oh, Tiger Lily.

45:52.089 --> 45:54.342
Help...

46:00.849 --> 46:04.479
Peter. Wait for me.

46:33.229 --> 46:36.859
That cursed Peter Pan.

46:38.235 --> 46:40.988
Making a fool out of me.

46:47.413 --> 46:50.292
Oh, my head.

46:55.923 --> 46:59.762
Oh, a pirate's life
is a wonderful life

46:59.845 --> 47:02.223
- Your hot water, Mr Smee.
- Shh!

47:02.307 --> 47:05.185
The poor Captain
has a splitting headache.

47:05.268 --> 47:08.481
We mustn't annoy him.

47:25.626 --> 47:30.340
Well, Captain, it's nice
to see you smiling again.

47:30.423 --> 47:34.929
Brings back the good old days when
we was leadin' a healthy, normal life.

47:35.012 --> 47:38.391
Scuttlin' ships, cuttin' throats.
Oh, Captain...

47:38.475 --> 47:40.894
why don't we put to sea again?

47:40.977 --> 47:44.232
You know, there's trouble
brewin' on the island.

47:44.315 --> 47:46.235
Women trouble.

47:46.318 --> 47:49.613
I wouldn't want this
to go any farther, but...

47:49.696 --> 47:53.576
the cook told me that
the first mate told him...

47:53.660 --> 47:57.998
that he heard that Pan
has banished Tinker Bell.

47:58.082 --> 48:01.085
Whoa!

48:01.168 --> 48:06.509
Why, you doddering imbecile, I...
Did you say Pan...

48:06.592 --> 48:09.303
has banished Tinker Bell?

48:09.387 --> 48:11.097
Aye, aye, Captain.
That he has.

48:11.180 --> 48:13.976
- But why?
- Well, on account of Wendy, Captain.

48:14.059 --> 48:18.107
Tink tried to do her in, she did.
Tink's terrible jealous.

48:18.190 --> 48:22.571
- Well, well.
- That's why we ought to leave, Captain.

48:22.654 --> 48:25.782
This ain't no place
for a respectable pirate.

48:25.866 --> 48:28.453
That's it, Smee!
That's it!

48:28.536 --> 48:30.496
I'm glad you agrees, Captain.

48:30.580 --> 48:33.625
Quick, me coat.
Me best dress coat.

48:33.709 --> 48:36.295
Aye, aye, sir. The sooner
we get going, the better.

48:36.379 --> 48:40.675
Ah, yes, a jealous female
can be tricked into anything.

48:40.759 --> 48:43.345
- My case of hooks!
- Aye, aye, sir.

48:43.429 --> 48:46.223
Here you are, sir.
Your Sunday set, sir.

48:46.307 --> 48:49.936
If we impress the pixie, convince her
we're eager to help her...

48:50.020 --> 48:53.065
the wench may chart
our course to a...

48:53.149 --> 48:55.985
certain hiding place.

48:56.068 --> 48:58.655
Our best hiding place
is the Spanish main, sir.

48:58.739 --> 49:00.991
I'll set our course...

49:01.074 --> 49:05.747
And where do you think
you are going?

49:05.830 --> 49:09.001
T-To tell the boys
we sails with the tide, sir.

49:09.084 --> 49:14.007
You will go ashore,
pick up Tinker Bell...

49:14.090 --> 49:17.428
and bring her to me.

49:18.554 --> 49:20.890
Understand?

49:20.973 --> 49:23.352
Aye, aye, s-s-s-sir.

49:33.823 --> 49:36.701
- How!
- How!

49:38.829 --> 49:40.747
What's the Chief doing, John?

49:40.831 --> 49:45.045
He's delivering an oration
in sign language.

49:45.129 --> 49:48.716
- What's he saying?
- He says...

49:48.800 --> 49:52.388
"Peter Pan, mighty warrior.

49:52.471 --> 49:54.557
"Save Tiger Lily.

49:54.640 --> 49:58.395
Make big Chief heap glad".

49:58.478 --> 50:01.732
Well, he certainly
doesn't look "heap glad".

50:01.816 --> 50:05.903
Make Peter Pan heap big chief.

50:05.987 --> 50:08.740
You now Little Flying Eagle.

50:10.826 --> 50:13.580
- Hurray for Flying Eagle! Flying Eagle!
- Hurray!

50:13.663 --> 50:16.040
Hurray!

50:16.124 --> 50:20.087
- Oh, how wonderful!
- Hurray!

50:30.266 --> 50:34.271
Teach 'em paleface brother
all about red man.

50:34.354 --> 50:37.275
Good, this should be
most enlightening.

50:37.358 --> 50:39.944
Uh, what makes the red man red?

50:40.028 --> 50:42.281
- When did he first say, "Ugh"?
- First say, "Ugh"?

50:42.364 --> 50:44.617
Why does he ask you, "How"?

50:44.700 --> 50:47.954
"Why does he ask you, 'How'?"

