51:55.411 --> 51:59.374
<i>What made the red man red</i>

51:59.457 --> 52:03.254
<i>Let's go back a million years
to the very first Injun prince</i>

52:03.337 --> 52:06.716
<i>He kissed a maid and start to blush
and we've all been blushin' since</i>

52:06.799 --> 52:09.720
<i>Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda</i>

52:09.803 --> 52:11.472
<i>Now you've got it right
from the head man</i>

52:11.555 --> 52:13.266
<i>The real true story
of the red man</i>

52:13.349 --> 52:17.813
<i>No matter what's been
written or said, no matter what</i>

52:17.897 --> 52:25.906
<i>Now you know why
the red man's red</i>

52:36.168 --> 52:39.256
- Wa-hoo!
- John!

52:39.340 --> 52:42.594
Squaw take 'em papoose.
Wa-hoo!

52:42.677 --> 52:46.933
- Michael!
- Squaw, get 'em firewood.

52:47.016 --> 52:50.102
Squaw no get 'em firewood!

52:50.186 --> 52:52.773
Squaw go home.

53:02.326 --> 53:04.495
Beggin' your pardon, Miss Bell...

53:04.578 --> 53:07.499
but Captain Hook
would like a word with ya.

53:21.473 --> 53:24.978
Yes, Miss Bell,
Captain Hook admits defeat.

53:26.771 --> 53:31.527
Tomorrow I leave the island,
never to return.

53:31.610 --> 53:34.990
I'm glad to hear that, Captain.
I'll tell the crew and...

53:40.204 --> 53:42.708
And that's why I asked
you over, me dear...

53:42.791 --> 53:46.295
to tell Peter
I bear him no ill will.

53:48.089 --> 53:52.595
Oh, Pan has his faults,
to be sure.

53:52.678 --> 53:55.598
Uh, bringing that Wendy
to the island, for instance.

53:55.681 --> 53:57.601
Dangerous business, that.

54:01.146 --> 54:06.737
Why, rumour has it that already
she has come between you and Peter.

54:10.783 --> 54:14.997
But what's this?
Tears?

54:15.080 --> 54:19.377
Then it is true.
Oh, Smee.

54:19.461 --> 54:22.548
The way of a man with a maid.

54:22.632 --> 54:27.387
Taking the best years
of her life and then...

54:27.471 --> 54:31.892
casting her aside
like an old glove!

54:31.975 --> 54:34.896
Ain't it a bloomin' shame?

54:34.979 --> 54:39.235
But we mustn't judge
Peter too harshly, me dear.

54:39.318 --> 54:43.031
It's that Wendy who's to blame.

54:43.114 --> 54:47.077
Mr Smee, we must
save the lad from himself.

54:47.160 --> 54:49.664
But how?

54:49.747 --> 54:53.335
We've so little time.
We sail in the morning.

54:53.418 --> 54:56.463
Sail! That's it, Smee!

54:58.925 --> 55:03.055
- We'll shanghai Wendy.
- "Shanghai Wendy," Captain?

55:03.138 --> 55:05.641
Take her to sea with us. With her gone,

55:05.642 --> 55:08.603
Peter will soon forget
this mad infatuation.

55:08.687 --> 55:12.358
Come, Smee, we must leave immediately.
Surround Peter's home...

55:12.441 --> 55:17.948
But, Captain, we...
we don't know where Peter Pan lives!

55:18.031 --> 55:21.660
Great Scott,
you're right, Smee!

55:21.743 --> 55:23.121
What's that, my dear?

55:25.707 --> 55:29.795
You could show us the way?
Why, I never thought of that.

55:29.879 --> 55:33.800
- Take this down, Smee.
- "Take this down, Smee".

55:33.885 --> 55:35.970
Aye, aye, Captain.

55:42.060 --> 55:45.315
- Start at Pegleg Point.
- "Start at Pegleg Point".

55:47.066 --> 55:50.362
- Forty paces west of Blindman's Bluff.
- "Blindman's Bluff".

55:50.446 --> 55:55.702
Yes, yes. Hop, skip and
a jump across Crocodile Creek.

55:55.785 --> 56:00.374
Then north by northeast,
one, two, three.

56:00.458 --> 56:04.463
Well, get on with it...
Continue, my dear.

56:07.383 --> 56:10.220
I mustn't harm Peter?

56:10.303 --> 56:14.350
Madam, Captain Hook
gives his word...

56:14.433 --> 56:17.228
not to lay a finger...

56:17.311 --> 56:20.065
or a hook on Peter Pan.

56:23.903 --> 56:26.906
Ah, Hangman's Tree.

56:26.989 --> 56:31.453
So that's the entrance
to his hiding place.

56:31.537 --> 56:35.375
Thank you, me dear.
You've been most helpful.

56:42.007 --> 56:45.554
<i>Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda</i>

56:45.637 --> 56:49.392
<i>Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda</i>

