<i>- Hana mana ganda, Hana mana ganda
- Hana mana ganda</i>

56:52.270 --> 56:55.315
<i>- Hana mana ganda
- What makes red men red</i>

56:55.399 --> 56:59.153
<i>Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda</i>

56:59.237 --> 57:03.118
<i>Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda, hana mana ganda</i>

57:03.201 --> 57:05.120
<i>Hana mana ganda
Hana mana ganda</i>

57:06.913 --> 57:10.293
Big Chief Flying Eagle
greets his braves.

57:10.376 --> 57:13.547
- How!
- Uh, how, Chief.
- How, Chief! How!

57:13.630 --> 57:15.173
- How.
- How.

57:15.257 --> 57:18.219
Big Chief greets Little Mother.

57:18.303 --> 57:20.763
- How!
- Ugh!

57:20.847 --> 57:24.101
Aw, Wendy, is that
all you have to say?

57:24.184 --> 57:27.731
- Everyone else thinks I'm wonderful.
- Especially Tiger Lily.

57:27.814 --> 57:30.817
- Tiger Lily?
- John! Michael!

57:30.901 --> 57:33.237
Take off that war paint
and get ready for bed.

57:33.321 --> 57:36.073
- Bed?
- Brave no sleep.

57:36.157 --> 57:38.410
Go for days without sleep.

57:38.493 --> 57:40.621
- But, boys, we're going home in the morning.
- Home!

57:40.704 --> 57:44.500
- And...
- Oh, Wendy, we don't want to go home.

57:44.584 --> 57:49.173
No go home. Stay many moons.
Have heap big time.

57:49.256 --> 57:52.009
Now, Peter, let's stop
pretending and be practical.

57:52.092 --> 57:55.513
Chief Flying Eagle has spoken.

57:55.597 --> 57:58.851
Oh, for goodness sake.
Please, boys.

57:58.935 --> 58:02.689
Do you want to stay here
and grow up like... like savages?

58:02.773 --> 58:04.691
- Of course.
- But you can't.

58:04.775 --> 58:08.238
You need a mother.
We all do.

58:08.321 --> 58:10.490
Aren't you our mother, Wendy?

58:10.573 --> 58:12.660
Why, Michael, of course not!

58:12.743 --> 58:14.912
Surely you haven't forgotten
our real mother!

58:14.995 --> 58:20.585
Did she have silky ears
and wear a fur coat?

58:20.669 --> 58:24.423
Oh, no, Michael.
That was Nana.

58:24.507 --> 58:26.425
I think I had a mother once.

58:26.509 --> 58:30.431
- What was she like?
- What was she like?
- I forget.

58:30.515 --> 58:33.477
- I had a white rat!
- That's no mother!

58:33.561 --> 58:36.105
Hey, who ya shovin'?

58:37.648 --> 58:42.028
No, no, boys! Please.
I'll tell you what a mother is.

58:42.112 --> 58:44.657
- Yeah, tell us.
- Yeah, tell us.
- Please, Wendy.

58:44.907 --> 58:48.036
Well, a mother,
a real mother...

58:48.120 --> 58:51.707
is the most wonderful person
in the world.

58:51.790 --> 58:55.378
She's the angel voice...

58:55.461 --> 58:57.840
that bids you good night...

58:57.923 --> 59:00.843
kisses your cheek...

59:00.926 --> 59:03.221
whispers, "Sleep tight".

59:04.431 --> 59:07.559
<i>Your mother</i>

59:07.642 --> 59:11.522
<i>And mine</i>

59:11.606 --> 59:16.528
<i>Your mother</i>

59:16.612 --> 59:20.658
<i>And mine</i>

59:20.742 --> 59:26.832
<i>The helping hand
that guides you along</i>

59:26.916 --> 59:34.008
<i>Whether you're right
Whether you're wrong</i>

59:34.091 --> 59:37.846
<i>Your mother</i>

59:37.930 --> 59:42.017
<i>And mine</i>

59:42.100 --> 59:47.190
<i>Your mother</i>

59:47.273 --> 59:51.862
<i>And mine</i>

59:51.946 --> 59:57.370
<i>What makes mothers
all that they are</i>

59:57.453 --> 01:00:06.798
<i>Might as well ask
what makes a star</i>

01:00:06.881 --> 01:00:12.888
<i>Ask your heart
to tell you her worth</i>

01:00:12.973 --> 01:00:16.226
<i>Your heart will say</i>

01:00:16.309 --> 01:00:20.898
<i>Heaven on earth</i>

01:00:20.982 --> 01:00:25.404
<i>Another word</i>

01:00:25.487 --> 01:00:30.285
<i>For divine</i>

01:00:30.368 --> 01:00:36.250
<i>Your mother</i>

01:00:36.333 --> 01:00:39.337
<i>And mine</i>

01:00:43.509 --> 01:00:48.432
- I wanna see my mother.
- Yes, Michael.

01:00:48.515 --> 01:00:50.934
I propose we leave
for home at once.

01:00:51.018 --> 01:00:53.980
- Could I go too? Huh, Wendy?
- Me too, Wendy!
- Come on! Let me go!

01:00:54.063 --> 01:00:58.277
All right, boys. All right. I'm sure
Mother would be glad to have you.

01:00:58.360 --> 01:01:01.322
Uh, that is,
if Peter doesn't mind.

01:01:01.405 --> 01:01:04.284
Go on!
Go back and grow up!

01:01:04.367 --> 01:01:07.579
But I'm warning ya.
Once you're grown up...

01:01:07.662 --> 01:01:09.832
you can never come back!

01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:13.253
- Never!
- Dear.

01:01:13.337 --> 01:01:17.090
- Well, then, shall we be off?
- Yeah, come on. Let's go!

01:01:17.174 --> 01:01:19.260
- Yeah!
- See ya, Peter.

01:01:20.845 --> 01:01:22.764
They'll be back.

01:01:27.854 --> 01:01:29.774
Peter.

01:01:33.027 --> 01:01:35.614
Goodbye, Peter.

01:01:43.374 --> 01:01:45.292
All right, men.
Take them away.

01:01:47.211 --> 01:01:52.968
And now, Smee, to take care
of Master Peter Pan.

01:01:53.051 --> 01:01:58.850
But, Captain, wouldn't it
be more humane-like to slit his throat?

01:01:58.934 --> 01:02:01.645
Aye, that it would, Mr Smee.

01:02:01.728 --> 01:02:05.483
But I have given me word
not to lay a finger...

01:02:05.566 --> 01:02:08.988
or a hook on Peter Pan.

01:02:10.239 --> 01:02:15.078
And Captain Hook
never breaks a promise.

01:02:15.328 --> 01:02:19.083
<i>Yo ho, yo ho
Yo ho, yo ho, yo ho</i>

01:02:19.166 --> 01:02:21.252
<i>So try the life of a thief</i>

01:02:21.335 --> 01:02:23.255
<i>Just sample the life of a crook</i>

01:02:23.338 --> 01:02:25.340
<i>There isn't a boy
who won't enjoy</i>

01:02:25.424 --> 01:02:28.261
<i>A-workin'for Captain Hook</i>

01:02:28.344 --> 01:02:31.431
<i>The world's most famous crook</i>

01:02:31.514 --> 01:02:36.103
Crook, crook, crickety crockety, crickety,
crick the croc is after Captain...

01:02:37.438 --> 01:02:39.441
<i>A special offer for today</i>

01:02:39.524 --> 01:02:41.651
<i>I'll tell you what I'll do</i>

01:02:41.735 --> 01:02:44.614
<i>All those who sign without delay</i>

01:02:44.697 --> 01:02:47.325
<i>Will get a free tattoo</i>

01:02:47.408 --> 01:02:49.995
<i>Why, it's like money in the bank</i>

01:02:50.078 --> 01:02:52.957
<i>Come on
Join up and I'll be frank</i>

01:02:53.041 --> 01:02:57.171
<i>Unless you do
you'll walk the plank</i>

01:02:57.254 --> 01:02:59.174
<i>The choice is up to you</i>

01:02:59.257 --> 01:03:01.468
<i>The choice is up to you</i>

01:03:01.551 --> 01:03:05.348
<i>Yo ho, yo ho
Yo ho, yo ho, yo ho</i>

01:03:05.431 --> 01:03:07.350
<i>You'll love the life of a thief</i>

01:03:07.433 --> 01:03:09.561
<i>You'll relish the life
of a crook</i>

01:03:09.645 --> 01:03:11.480
<i>There's barrels
of fun for everyone</i>

01:03:11.563 --> 01:03:15.193
<i>And you'll get treasures
by the ton</i>

01:03:15.276 --> 01:03:19.406
<i>So come and sign the book</i>

01:03:19.490 --> 01:03:22.451
<i>Join up with Captain Hook</i>

01:03:22.534 --> 01:03:24.746
- Hey, I wanna join!
- Please! Oh, boy!

01:03:24.829 --> 01:03:28.124
- I wanna be a pirate!
- Oh, boy! A pirate!

01:03:28.208 --> 01:03:33.172
Boys! Aren't you
ashamed of yourselves?

01:03:33.255 --> 01:03:36.426
But Captain Hook is
most insistent, Wendy.

01:03:36.510 --> 01:03:39.847
Yeah! He says we'll walk
the plank if we don't.

01:03:39.931 --> 01:03:43.435
Oh, no, we won't.
Peter Pan will save us.

01:03:43.519 --> 01:03:47.272
Peter Pan will save them, Smee.

01:03:48.525 --> 01:03:50.777
Peter Pan will save them.

01:03:52.821 --> 01:03:54.740
Oh, Captain, you did it.

01:03:54.824 --> 01:03:57.576
But a thousand pardons, my dear.

01:03:57.660 --> 01:04:00.956
I don't believe you are
in on our little joke.

01:04:01.039 --> 01:04:05.295
You see, we left
a present for Peter.

01:04:05.378 --> 01:04:08.214
Sort of a surprise package,
you might say.

01:04:08.298 --> 01:04:11.760
Why, I can see our little
friend at this very moment...

01:04:11.844 --> 01:04:16.099
reading the tender inscription.

01:04:16.182 --> 01:04:20.814
"To Peter, with love
from Wendy.

01:04:20.897 --> 01:04:24.485
Do not open till 6 o'clock".

01:04:25.695 --> 01:04:27.613
Huh. I wonder what's in it.

01:04:27.697 --> 01:04:30.826
Could he but see
within the package...

01:04:30.909 --> 01:04:35.290
he would find an ingenious
little device.

01:04:35.373 --> 01:04:38.293
Set, so that when
the clock is like this...

01:04:38.376 --> 01:04:41.631
Peter Pan will be blasted...

01:04:41.714 --> 01:04:45.510
out of Never Land forever.

01:04:45.594 --> 01:04:46.345
No!

01:04:51.059 --> 01:04:53.436
But time grows short.

01:04:53.519 --> 01:04:58.067
We have but 18 seconds.

01:04:58.150 --> 01:05:01.446
Fifteen seconds.

01:05:01.529 --> 01:05:04.325
Thirteen seconds.

01:05:04.408 --> 01:05:06.327
Twelve seconds.

01:05:06.410 --> 01:05:08.371
Well, I guess
I can open it now.

01:05:14.671 --> 01:05:17.423
Hey, Tink.
Look what Wendy left.

01:05:17.507 --> 01:05:20.928
Hey, stop that! Stop it!
What's the matter with you?

01:05:21.011 --> 01:05:23.180
Hook? A bomb?

01:05:23.263 --> 01:05:25.433
Don't be ridiculous!

01:05:34.569 --> 01:05:37.948
And so passeth a worthy opponent.

01:05:38.031 --> 01:05:39.951
Amen.

01:05:43.872 --> 01:05:46.793
Hook! It was a bomb!

01:05:46.876 --> 01:05:51.298
Why, if it hadn't been
for Tink... Tinker Bell!

01:05:55.721 --> 01:05:58.640
Tink? Tinker Bell?

01:06:01.561 --> 01:06:03.563
Where are you, Tink?

01:06:03.646 --> 01:06:06.984
Tink? Tinker Bell!

01:06:14.035 --> 01:06:17.330
Tink. Are you all right?

01:06:17.413 --> 01:06:21.293
Wendy? The boys?

01:06:24.047 --> 01:06:26.090
But I've gotta save you first.

01:06:26.174 --> 01:06:28.301
Hold on, Tink! Hold on!

01:06:28.384 --> 01:06:31.638
Don't go out.
Don't you understand, Tink?

01:06:31.722 --> 01:06:35.310
You mean more to me than
anything in this whole world!

01:06:37.896 --> 01:06:43.027
And now, which will it be?
The pen or the plank?

01:06:43.110 --> 01:06:46.740
Captain Hook, we will
never join your crew.

01:06:46.823 --> 01:06:50.161
As you wish.
Ladies first, my dear.

01:06:50.244 --> 01:06:53.665
- Goodbye, boys.
- Goodbye, Wendy.
- Goodbye, Wendy.

01:06:53.748 --> 01:06:57.711
- Be brave, John.
- I shall strive to, Wendy.

01:06:57.795 --> 01:07:01.341
- Goodbye, Michael.
- Goodbye, Wendy.
- Come on!

01:07:01.424 --> 01:07:04.095
- Get along over there!
- Get going, miss. Get going! Don't give us no trouble!

01:07:04.178 --> 01:07:07.014
Go on! Go on!
Get it over with!

01:07:07.098 --> 01:07:10.018
- Move along!
- The Captain's waitin'!

01:07:17.528 --> 01:07:20.281
Wendy! Wendy!

01:07:24.704 --> 01:07:28.874
- Captain, n-no splash.
- Not a sound.

01:07:28.959 --> 01:07:32.212
- Not a bloomin' ripple.
- It's a jinx, that's what it is.

01:07:32.295 --> 01:07:35.049
- No splash.
- No sign of the wench.

01:07:35.133 --> 01:07:38.971
- Did you hear a splash?
- I'm telling you, mates, it's a black day.

01:07:39.054 --> 01:07:41.557
Mark me words.
We'll all pay for this.

01:07:41.640 --> 01:07:43.934
The ship is bewitched.

01:07:44.019 --> 01:07:46.104
No splash, Captain.

01:07:46.187 --> 01:07:51.318
So, you want a splash, Mr Starkey.

01:07:51.402 --> 01:07:53.696
I'll give you a splash!

01:07:53.779 --> 01:07:56.324
- Who's next?
- You're next, Hook!

01:07:56.533 --> 01:08:00.330
- This time you've gone too far!
- It's Pan! Peter Pan!

01:08:00.413 --> 01:08:02.415
- And Wendy!
- It can't be!

01:08:02.498 --> 01:08:04.710
It's his blinkin' ghost
what's talkin'!

01:08:04.793 --> 01:08:06.628
Say your prayers, Hook.

01:08:06.712 --> 01:08:11.134
I'll show you this ghost
has blood in his veins.

01:08:11.217 --> 01:08:14.180
I'll run him through! Ooh!

01:08:14.263 --> 01:08:16.265
Take that!

01:08:23.189 --> 01:08:24.817
Curse this hook!

01:08:26.611 --> 01:08:28.613
Come on, everybody!

01:08:32.033 --> 01:08:34.953
Hurry, Michael! Hurry!

01:08:35.037 --> 01:08:37.999
Don't stand there,
you bilge rats!

01:08:38.082 --> 01:08:41.170
Get those scurvy brats!

01:08:41.252 --> 01:08:44.133
After the brats, men!

01:09:09.413 --> 01:09:11.457
This is no mere boy.

01:09:11.541 --> 01:09:15.170
'Tis some fiend fighting me.
A flying devil!

01:09:23.054 --> 01:09:25.140
- Hold your fire.
- Get 'em!

01:09:25.224 --> 01:09:28.394
Steady, men. Steady.

01:09:28.477 --> 01:09:30.479
- Club 'em with the marline.
- Fire!

01:09:30.564 --> 01:09:34.151
- I'll crack their bloomin' skulls!
- Let me at 'em!

01:09:34.234 --> 01:09:36.863
Down, you blackguard!

01:10:13.074 --> 01:10:14.785
Hurray!

01:10:19.707 --> 01:10:24.546
- Right through, Michael.
- Yea, Bear Killer!
- Yea for Bear Killer!

01:10:24.630 --> 01:10:27.800
Fly! Fly! Fly! You coward!

01:10:27.883 --> 01:10:29.594
Coward? Me?

01:10:29.761 --> 01:10:34.892
Ha-ha-ha! You wouldn't dare fight
old Hook man-to-man!

01:10:34.975 --> 01:10:37.520
You'd fly away like
a cowardly sparrow!

01:10:37.603 --> 01:10:40.690
Nobody calls Pan
a coward and lives!

01:10:40.774 --> 01:10:43.735
I'll fight you man-to-man,
with one hand behind my back.

01:10:45.279 --> 01:10:50.077
- You mean you won't fly?
- No, don't, Peter! It's a trick!

01:10:50.160 --> 01:10:54.416
- I give my word, Hook.
- Good, then let's have at it!

01:11:15.065 --> 01:11:20.363
Now! Insolent youth,
prepare to die!

01:11:20.447 --> 01:11:23.158
Fly! Fly, Peter! Fly!

01:11:23.241 --> 01:11:27.329
No! I gave my word.

01:11:30.208 --> 01:11:33.045
You're mine, Hook!

01:11:34.630 --> 01:11:37.968
Cleave him to the brisket!

01:11:38.052 --> 01:11:42.682
You wouldn't do old Hook
in now, would you, lad?

01:11:42.766 --> 01:11:47.271
I'll go away forever.
I'll do anything you say.

01:11:47.354 --> 01:11:53.028
Well, all right.
If ya say you're a codfish.

01:11:53.111 --> 01:11:56.491
- I'm a codfish.
- Louder!

01:11:56.574 --> 01:12:00.996
- I'm a codfish!
- Hurray!

01:12:01.080 --> 01:12:05.418
Hook is a codfish
A codfish, a codfish

01:12:05.502 --> 01:12:09.757
- Hook is a codfish, a codfish, a codfish
- All right, Hook...

01:12:09.840 --> 01:12:14.053
you're free to go,
and never return.

01:12:17.557 --> 01:12:19.559
Peter!

01:12:27.861 --> 01:12:30.407
Smee! Smee!

01:12:44.172 --> 01:12:46.092
Smee!

01:12:47.844 --> 01:12:52.933
Smee! Smee!

01:12:53.016 --> 01:12:57.105
Smee-ee-ee-ee-ee-ee-ee-ee!

01:12:57.188 --> 01:12:59.775
Captain!

01:12:59.859 --> 01:13:01.944
Captain! Captain!

01:13:03.446 --> 01:13:04.949
Hurray!

01:13:06.033 --> 01:13:09.537
Hurray for Captain Pan!

01:13:09.620 --> 01:13:12.875
All right, ya swabs,
aloft with ya!

01:13:12.958 --> 01:13:17.005
We're castin' off!
Heave those halyards!

01:13:17.088 --> 01:13:21.051
But, but, Peter...
Oh, that is, Captain Pan.

01:13:21.135 --> 01:13:26.224
- At your service, madam.
- Could you tell me, sir, where we're sailing?

01:13:26.308 --> 01:13:30.229
- To London, madam.
- Oh, Peter.

01:13:30.313 --> 01:13:34.233
Michael! John!
We're going home!

01:13:34.317 --> 01:13:37.071
Man the capstan!

01:13:37.154 --> 01:13:39.908
Hoist anchor!

01:13:42.660 --> 01:13:44.704
Pixie dust!

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:25.421
George, I am so glad
you changed your mind

01:14:25.422 --> 01:14:27.923
about Wendy. After all,
she's still a child.

01:14:28.006 --> 01:14:32.221
Oh, pshaw, Mary.
You know I never mean those things.

01:14:32.304 --> 01:14:34.265
Do I, Nana?

01:14:36.685 --> 01:14:40.106
Oh! Wendy!

01:14:42.483 --> 01:14:45.737
Wendy, what on earth
are you doing there?

01:14:45.821 --> 01:14:48.282
Mmm. Hmm?

01:14:50.660 --> 01:14:53.288
- Oh, Mother, we're back!
- Back?

01:14:53.371 --> 01:14:56.250
All except the Lost Boys.
They weren't quite ready.

01:14:56.333 --> 01:14:58.794
- Lost Bo... Ready?
- To grow up.

01:14:58.878 --> 01:15:01.214
That's why they went
back to Never Land.

01:15:01.298 --> 01:15:04.384
- Never Land?
- Yes, but I am.

01:15:04.468 --> 01:15:08.097
- Uh, "am"?
- Uh, ready to grow up.

01:15:08.181 --> 01:15:10.434
Oh! Oh! Uh...

01:15:10.517 --> 01:15:14.104
Well, my dear,
all in good time.

01:15:14.188 --> 01:15:16.941
- After all, perhaps we were too...
- Oh, but, Mother...

01:15:17.025 --> 01:15:19.611
it was such a wonderful adventure.

01:15:19.694 --> 01:15:22.448
Tinker Bell and the mermaids
and Peter Pan.

01:15:22.531 --> 01:15:24.450
Oh, he was the most
wonderful of all.

01:15:24.533 --> 01:15:27.621
- Why, why, even when we were kidnapped, I...
- Kidnapped!

01:15:27.704 --> 01:15:31.375
Mm-hmm. I knew Peter Pan
would save us, and he did.

01:15:31.459 --> 01:15:34.295
And we all called him a codfish!

01:15:34.378 --> 01:15:36.465
Uh, Captain Hook, I mean.

01:15:36.548 --> 01:15:40.386
And then we sailed away
on a ship in the sky.

01:15:40.470 --> 01:15:44.974
Hmm. Mary, I'm going to bed.

01:15:45.058 --> 01:15:49.980
Oh, Mother.
He really is wonderful, isn't he?

01:15:50.064 --> 01:15:53.235
See how well he sails the ship.

01:15:53.318 --> 01:15:57.990
- George. George!
- Now what, Mary?

01:16:00.829 --> 01:16:03.039
Nana, d-did you see...

01:16:05.417 --> 01:16:07.837
You know, I have
the strangest feeling...

01:16:07.920 --> 01:16:10.340
that I've seen that ship before.

01:16:10.423 --> 01:16:12.759
A long time ago...

01:16:12.843 --> 01:16:15.388
when I was very young.

01:16:15.471 --> 01:16:19.767
- George, dear.
- Father.

01:16:19.851 --> 01:16:23.105
<i>When there's a smile in your heart</i>

01:16:23.188 --> 01:16:28.445
<i>There's no better time to start</i>

01:16:28.528 --> 01:16:30.614
<i>Think of all the joy you'll find</i>

01:16:30.698 --> 01:16:32.616
<i>When you leave the world behind</i>

01:16:32.700 --> 01:16:36.204
<i>And bid your cares goodbye</i>

01:16:36.288 --> 01:16:38.957
<i>You can fly</i>

01:16:39.040 --> 01:16:41.461
<i>You can fly</i>

01:16:42.712 --> 01:16:47.468
<i>You can fly</i>

